Frequently Asked Questions

What happens at the end of my trial?

At the end of your 7-day trial, you’ll automatically be downgraded to the Basic tier and you’ll be able to continue to use ChargeAutomation as long as you’d like. If you decide to upgrade to a paid plan, you can do so from the billing page in your account at any time during or after your trial. Nothing! You can continue to use the pre-arrival feature.
If you are taking payments or authorization, you will receive usage based monthly bill at the end of every month.

Why Use ChargeAutomation?

ChargeAutomation is the only digital journey solution in the industry that combines collecting pre-arrival info, payments, security deposit, offering upsell & providing personalized customer portal all in one easy-to-use flow.

Can we manage multiple properties?

Yes you can manage multiple properties with its own set of rules.

Does ChargeAutomation collect my funds?

No, ChargeAutomation uses your connected payment gateway, so you are in control of your funds at all time.

Can I use ChargeAutomation as a standalone?

Yes, you can use ChargeAutomation as a standalone solution to collect pre-arrival, payments and security deposit and offer guidebook & chat.

Is it Secure & GDPR Complaint?

 We are PCI Compliance and we do not store credit card data.We are also GDPR compliant and you are in control of your data at all time.

What PMS or gateway do you integrate with?

You can find the list of all platforms we integrate with here.

If you do not find what you’re looking for, send us a request via support@chargeautomation.com

Do I need to have a payment gateway to use your software?

If you want to collect or authorize payments, yes you will need to have one.

Otherwise you can still use it to collect pre-arrival info, guest portal and chat with your customers.
